history.content: The 61 series is generally pretty safe to phase 2.  No guarantees, but they usually expand them a lot to accommodate everyone they can since so many people watch webcasts/videos instead of live lecture.  Also helps that the 999 sections make it so you don't lose out on a discussion/lab time that fits your schedule.

The way time conflict works is that unless both classes don't allow time conflicts, you don't need special approval.  The assumption should probably be that the instructors who don't allow time conflicts want you to show up to class and the one's who do would be ok if you watched it online. Students have to take responsibility for the possibility of conflicting final exams and it is likely though not certain that the instructors who don't allow time conflicts would be less likely to offer alternative times for those exams.

Hi, I have a time conflict with CS61B and Chem 3AL. I think I should be able to get an override approved, but I didn't realize that Chem 3AL doesn't allow time conflicts till about an hour ago, and I have low expectations for the chem advisors I emailed just now to get anything processed before my 11:30AM enrollment tomorrow. 

I'm wondering if I'd probably be okay to Phase II CS61B, or if anyone has advice/has been in a similar situation.
history.subject: Time conflict with a Non EECS
